      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "that makes sense, thanks. so if the attachment is at the VP level, the whole branch for the verb phrase just expands to include the PP? i'm having a hard time visualizing how the nodes actually connect in the hierarchy when the phrase is \"higher up\" vs tucked into the NP. can you walk me through the node connections for the VP attachment version specifically?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When attaching to the VP, the entire VP node essentially expands to contain both the main verb and the newly attached Prepositional Phrase (PP). Imagine the VP node having multiple children: one child for the direct object (the man) and another child directly under the VP heading representing the PP (\"with the telescope\"). This structure shows the PP is integral to *how* the verb happened, making it a modifier of the action itself.",
