    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To keep the diagram clean, most linguists try to draw the attached PP immediately adjacent to the node it modifies. For VP attachment, you usually nest the PP directly underneath the VP node, perhaps as a sister to the object or a complement to the verb. If the tree becomes too dense, sometimes using different styles for adjuncts versus complements can help visually separate the attachment points.",
